data.description: This beautiful 1916 bungalow has been thoughtfully remodeled to provide modern amenities while still maintaining its vintage charm. With four spacious bedrooms and two bathrooms, this home is perfect for those who appreciate ample space. Upon entering the home, you will be greeted with a warm and welcoming living room, kitchen and dining room area that features new luxury vinyl flooring and bright and cheery natural lighting. The kitchen has been updated with modern appliances and fresh paint throughout. The original part of the home offers an oversized living room, two cozy bedrooms, one full bathroom and an additional flex space that the current owner is using as a pantry yet with some creativity and ingenuity, this small space can be transformed into a functional area that meets a variety of needs. Some possible uses for this space could include a cozy reading nook, a home office, or even a mini gym.  In 2015, there were modern updates made to the addition that had been done sometime in the 70's that provided two additional bedrooms, an upstairs bathroom, an open living room, dining room and they moved the kitchen this part of the home. The bright and airy living space is perfect for entertaining guests or relaxing.  The exterior of the home is just as lovely with its inviting front porch that provides a great space for relaxing or simply enjoying the outdoors along with the freshly painted exterior really gives the curb appeal a WOW factor! The outdoor space is all set up with a large fenced backyard and dog kennel. There is a one car garage perfect to store your toys or create a workshop. The homeowners believe it was originally the carriage house.  Whether you prefer the classic charm of the original home or the modern elegance of the addition, this house offers the best of both worlds. With plenty of space for everyone, it's the perfect place to call home. Schedule an appointment today to take a look for yourself!
